      • getEllipse

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> getEllipse​(org.opencv.core.Mat img,
                                                               org.opencv.core.Mat mask,
                                                               int resizewidth,
                                                               int incli)
        * The function that finds the ellipse with the best score. This function calls the methods drawEllipse, getFirstPixel,getLeftPixel,getRightPixel
        Parameters:
        img - a picture with a glass on it
        mask - the mask to isolate the glass from the rest of the image
        resizewidth - the the width of the image resize, must take a value between 550 (above no interest) and 200 (below too small), to increase from 50 to 50
        incli - , 3 possible values: 1 if the glass is from the front or the photo taken at a slight angle; 2 if the glass is moderately inclined; 3 if the is very inclined or seen from above. The start and end values of the ellipse height depend on this.
        Returns:
        an double list containing the left and right points and the height of the ellipse
